<title type="html"><![CDATA[12/19 (Sat.) All You Need To Know About Japan’s ‘Nengajo’ /The Psychology of Home/(Host:Michelle Hsu)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=455&amp;p=473#p473"><![CDATA[
12/19 (Sat.) All You Need To Know About Japan’s ‘Nengajo’ /The Psychology of Home/(Host:Michelle Hsu)<br /><br />1.All You Need To Know About Japan’s ‘Nengajo’ New Year’s Cards(日式賀年卡:年賀狀)<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://savvytokyo.com/need-know-japans-nengajo-new-years-cards/">https://savvytokyo.com/need-know-japans ... ars-cards/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Q&amp;A:<br />1.Do you still send the cards for season's Greetings?<br />2.What do you feel about receive the physical card,or a digital card?<br />3.What kind of different benefit or between the physical card and a digital card?<br />4.How do you think the traditional Japanese style-negajo(年賀狀).<br /><br />2.The Psychology of Home: Why Where You Live Means So Much<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2011/12/the-psychology-of-home-why-where-you-live-means-so-much/249800/">https://www.theatlantic.com/health/arch ... ch/249800/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Q&amp;A:<br /><br />1. Please write down English words emerging in your mind while referring to the word “home”.<br /><br />2. Is your answer for &quot;where are you from?&quot; the same as &quot;where's home for you?&quot; Share your reason.<br /><br />3. What is conveyed by the saying, “People and the places where they reside are engaged in a continuing set of exchanges; they have determinate, mutual effects upon each other because they are part of a single, interactive system?”<br /><br />4. A psychologist says that home is part of one’s self-definition, and that is why we adorn where we live. So, how do you define yourself?<br /><br />5. What is the perfect home in your dream?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=25764">Michelle Hsu</a> — Fri Dec 18, 2020 4:55 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
